      <h2>
        <i>turn your spreadsheet into a fully customizable blog</i>
      </h2>
    </header>
    
    <main>
      <article>
        <h1 id="howtouse">How to Use</h1>
        <ul>
          <li>Make a copy of <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1VZcd3MKIrrgRd9DrnUoEjEvzO4Gm6iDDBhw56i9CFXY/copy">this Google Sheets template</a></li>
          <li>Select <strong>Share</strong></li>
          <li>Update the sheet's permissions to <strong>"anyone on the internet with this link can view"</strong> and copy the link</li>
          <li>Paste the link into the form below to get your unique blog URL</li>
          <li>Add/edit posts as rows in the <strong>Posts</strong> sheet</li>
          <li>Adjust your blog's look and feel in the <strong>CSS</strong> and <strong>SEO</strong> sheets</li>
          <li>To unpublish the sheet, change its permissions back to "restricted"</li>
        </ul>
        
        <form class="enter-url" method="post">
          <label for="url">
            Enter your spreadsheet's URL:
          </label><br/>
          <input id="url" name="url" required="required" type="text">
          <button type="submit">Submit</button>
        </form>
        
        <h1 id="sharediscover">Share &amp; Discover</h1>
        <p>Want to see other sheet-posting blogs, or share your own?<br/><a href="/~1cCUbZjwGl4Dkq-rbSMyeTCtQUBwIhVzlrVKQxhOb010">Check out the blogring!</a></p>
